         <div type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn">
             <p><!-- 
amwb : in Kielhorn's edition, I am not sure that the simple daṇḍa and double daṇḍa in the verse part are original or not. In the verse part, there is no supplied daṇda. In the prose part, it seems that he noted original daṇdas and supplied omitted daṇḍa in line 38, 40, 43, 49, 56, 57, 58.Consequently I assume that the daṇḍa in the verse part are orginal but we need to check that by reading the plate. 
             -->
                 <pb
n="1r"/><lb
n="1"/>oṁ<!-- 
amwb : kielhorn mentioned that it is noted by a symbol
--> svasti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
<lg n="1" met="vasantatilakā"><!-- 
amwb : 14 morae
-->
      <l n="a">sarvajñatāṁ śriyam iva sthiram āsthitasya</l>
      <l n="b">vajrāsa<lb
n="2" break="no"/>nasya <choice><orig>va</orig><reg>ba</reg></choice>hu-māra-kulopalambhāḥ<g type="danda">.</g></l>
      <l n="c">devyā mahā-karuṇayā paripā<lb
n="3" break="no"/>litāni</l>
      <l n="d">rakṣantu vo daśa valāni diśo jayanti<g type="ddanda">.</g></l>
</lg>
<lg n="2" met="mālinī"><!-- 
amwb : 15 morae
-->
      <l n="a">śriya iva subhagā<lb
n="4" break="no"/>yaḥ sambhavo vārirāśiś</l><!-- 
amwb : here one can observe an infrequent use of sandhi *iḥ + śa => iś śa
-->
      <l n="b">śaśadhara iva bhāso viśvam āhlādayantyāḥ<g type="danda">.</g></l>
      <l n="c">prakr̥tir avanipānāṁ santater uttamāyā</l>
      <l n="d">a<lb
n="5" break="no"/>jani dayitaviṣṇuḥ sarvvavidyāvadātaḥ<g type="ddanda">.</g></l>
</lg>
<lg n="3" met="anuṣṭubh">
      <l n="a">āsīd ā sāgarād urvvīṁ</l>
      <l n="b">gurrvībhiḥ kīrttibhiḥ kr̥tī<g type="danda">.</g></l>
      <l n="c">maṇḍayan<lb
n="6"/>khaṇḍitārātiḥ</l>
      <l n="d">ślāghyaḥ śrī-vapyaṭas tataḥ<g type="ddanda">.</g></l>
</lg>
<lg n="4" met="śārdūlavikrīḍita"><!-- 
amwb : 19 morae
-->    <l n="a">mātsya-nyāyam apohituṁ prakr̥tibhir lakṣmyāḥ karaṅ grāhitaḥ</l>
       <l n="b">śrī-gopā<lb
n="7" break="no"/>la iti kṣitīśa-śirasāṁ cūḍāmaṇis tat sutaḥ<g type="danda">.</g></l>
       <l n="c">yasyānukriyate sanātana-yaśo-rāśir diśam āśaye</l>
       <l n="d">śvetimnā ya<lb
n="8" break="no"/>di paurṇṇamāsa-rajanī jyotsnātibhāra-śriyā<g type="ddanda">.</g></l> 
</lg>
<lg n="5" met="śārdūlavikrīḍita">
       <l n="a">śītāṁśor iva rohiṇī hutabhujaḥ svāheva tejo-nidheḥ</l>
       <l n="b">śarvāṇī<lb
n="9" break="no"/>va śivasya guhakya-pater bhadreva bhadrātmajā<g type="danda">.</g></l>
       <l n="c">paulomīva purandarasya dayīta śrī-deddadevīty abhūd</l>
       <l n="d">devī tasya vino<lb
n="10" break="no"/>da-bhūr mura-ripor lakṣmīr iva kṣmā-pateḥ<g type="ddanda">.</g></l>
</lg>
<lg n="6" met="sragdharā"><!-- 
amwb : 21 morae
-->
       <l n="a">tabhyaṁ śrī-dharmmapālaḥ samajani sujana-stūyamānāvadānaḥ</l>
       <l n="b">svāmī bhūmī<lb
n="11" break="no"/>-patīnām<!-- 
amwb : kielhorn's note: 'originally patīnāṁ seems to have been engraved'
--> akhila-vasumatī-maṇḍalaṁ śāsad ekaḥ<g type="danda">.</g></l>
       <l n="c" real="++++-++------++-++-+=">catvāras tīra-majjat-kari-gaṇa-caraṇa-nyasta-mudrāḥ yātrāṁ</l><!-- 
amwb: here to have the count of syllables, we have to cut the word yasya and to assume an enjambement; but if we do so, a mora is missing in d ; so it seems to me more likely that yasya begins the pāda d and a mora is missing in c. Consequently I choose to begin d with yasya and to report a metrical problem in c EDG §6.1.4 on metrical problems : here I add no correction for the moment. When I compare the pāda with the prosody, I should have caraṇānyasta-(caraṇa + anyasta- ?) and the mora missing could be between mudrāḥ and yātrāṁ
(+ means long mora ; - means short mora ; = means short or long)
catvāras tīra-majjat-kari-gaṇa-caraṇa-nyasta-mudrāḥ     yātrāṁ
+   + +  +  - +   + |- -  - -  - - + | +   -  +  +   -  +  =
-->
       <l n="d">ya<lb
n="12" break="no"/>sya kṣamante na bhuvana-parikhā vi<choice><sic>śv</sic><corr>ṣv</corr></choice>ag āśā jigīṣoḥ<g type="ddanda">.</g></l>
</lg>
<lg n="7" met="sragdharā"><!-- 
amwb : 21 morae
-->
       <l n="a">yasminn uddāma-lilā-calita-<choice><orig>va</orig><reg>ba</reg></choice>la-bhare dig-jayāya pravr̥tte</l>
       <l n="b">yāntyā<lb
n="13"/><choice><orig><unclear>m v</unclear></orig><reg>ṁ v</reg></choice>iśvambharāyāṁ calita-giri-tiraścīnatāṁ tad-vaśena<g type="danda">.</g></l>
       <l n="c">bhārābhugnāvamajjan-maṇi-vidhura-śiraś-cakra-sāhāyakārthaṁ</l>
       <l n="d">śeṣe<lb
n="14" break="no"/>ṇodasta-doṣṇā tvaritataram adhodhas tam evānuyātam<g type="ddanda">.</g></l>
</lg>
<lg n="8" met="mandākrāntā"><!-- 
amwb : 17 morae
-->
       <l n="a">yat-prasthāne pracalita-<choice><orig>v</orig><corr>b</corr></choice>alāsphālanād ullaladbhir</l>
       <l n="b">dhūlī-puraiḥ pihi<lb
n="15" break="no"/>ta-sakala-vyomabhir bhūtadhātryāḥ<g type="danda">.</g></l>
       <l n="c">samprāptāyāḥ parama-tanutāṁ cakravālaṁ phaṇānāṁ</l>
       <l n="d">magnonmīlan-maṇi phaṇipater lā<lb
n="16"/>ghavād ullalāsa<g type="ddanda">.</g></l>
</lg>
<lg n="9" met="anuṣṭubh">
       <l n="a">viruddha-viṣaya-kṣobhād</l>
       <l n="b">yasya kopāgnir aurvavat<g type="danda">.</g></l>
       <l n="c">an<choice><sic>ir</sic><corr>i</corr></choice>vr̥ti prajajvāla</l>
       <l n="d">catur-ambhodhi-vāritaḥ<g type="ddanda">.</g></l>
</lg>
<lg n="10" met="śārdūlavikrīḍita"><!-- 
amwb : 19 morae
-->
       <l n="a"> <lb
n="17"/>ye bhūvan pr̥thu-rāma-rāghava-nala-prāya dharitrībhujas</l>
       <l n="b">tān ekatra didr̥kṣuṇeva nicitān sarvān sama<choice><orig>m</orig><reg>ṁ</reg></choice> vedhasā<g type="danda">.</g></l>
       <l n="c">dhva<lb
n="18" break="no"/>stāśeṣa-narendra-māna-mahimā śrī-dharmmapālaḥ kalau</l>
       <l n="d">lolaśrīkariṇī-nivandhana-mahāstambhaḥ samuttambhitaḥ<g type="ddanda">.</g></l>  
</lg>
